VSri Swayamprakasha Trust has released a CD (Audio, MP3, Rs. 199) of Adisankara's `Soundarya Lahari.' The hundred slokas have been sung in as many ragas by Meenakshi Ravi. She has been accompanied by N.G.Ravi on the mridangam, Veena Vahini on the veena, Pranesh on the flute, Jayashri on the keyboard, Venkatesh on the tabla and Priya on the rhythmpad. The album comes with a booklet containing the slokas in Hindi and the English transcription.The Trust is run by Sri Adishankaracharya Sharada Lakshminarasimha Peetam, Sree Math, Hariharapuram, on the banks of the Tunga, 19 km from Sringeri. The Sree Math maintains a Rig Veda patasala and a gosala. The Live Happily Foundation supports students to pursue higher education. For details contact P.N.Viswanathan, Administrator, Sree Math, Hariharapura-577120, Chikmagalur District, Karnataka. Phone: 08265274458/9448074458.Bottom Template Starts
